IN WHICH IS PROSECV|TED THE ILLVSTRIOVS d&eacute;edes of the knight of the Sunne, and his brother <HI>Rosicleer,</HI> Sonnes vnto the Empe|rour <HI>Trebatio</HI> of Greece: With the vali|ant deedes of armes of sundry worthie Knights, very delightfull to bee read, and nothing hurtfull to bee regarded.</P>
