<P><PB REF="178">But whe~ the king <HI>Liseo</HI> vnderstood that h&eacute;e was the <HI>knight</HI> of the <HI>Sunne,</HI> and with what determination h&eacute;e dyd offer himselfe in their aide and succour, in all his life h&eacute;e did not receiue greater ioye and pleasure, and went vnto him and embraced him, saying: Great and infinit thankes dooe I giue vnto my Lord God, for that it hath pleased him to let m&eacute;e s&eacute;e so high and worthie a <HI>Knight,</HI> and I may well per|swade my selfe, that you b&eacute;eing a <HI>knight</HI> of so strange and gentle disposition, can b&eacute;e no other, but h&eacute;e whose fame is in all the world, and not a little amazed at your straunge and excelle<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters">t bountie. And now s&eacute;eing that it is my fortune to come into this great extremitie, and that you of necessiti<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> must make an ende of this your pretend<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters">d enterprise, God forbid that euer you should leaue this your determined pre|tence for to accomhlish my neces<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters">itie&punc; it were much better that I loose my whole Kingdome, then to hazard the liue<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> of so precious and valyaunt <HI>knights.</HI> Therefore I will re|turne againe into <HI>Lidia,</HI> and procure to b&eacute;e with my <HI>knight<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"></HI> b&eacute;efore my time b&eacute;e expired, and there offer my selfe vnto death with them, for to accomplish &amp; performe that which I haue promised. Then the <HI>Knight</HI> of the <HI>Sunne</HI> who wa<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> wholie determined to goe with the King sayde. I am ful|lie determined to accomplish all that which I haue sayde&punc; and if it b&eacute;e so that you are not content therewith, h&eacute;ere <GAP DESC="